============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

Theorem/Law:  Quadratic Formula
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      x = (-b ± sqrt(b²-4ac))/2a
Applications: Engineering, physics
Discoverer:   Ancient Babylonians (2000)

Theorem/Law:  Fundamental Theorem of Calculus
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      ∫[a,b] f'(x)dx = f(b) - f(a)
Applications: Physics, engineering, economics
Discoverer:   Newton/Leibniz (1670)

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

